				\begin{document}$$ \frac{WG-\overline{WG}}{stdev(WG)}-\frac{VL-\overline{VL}}{stdev(VL)} $$\end{document}WG−WG¯stdevWG−VL−VL¯stdevVL. The WUR genotype was coded so that BB was −1, AB was 0 and AA was +1. Additionally, correlations were calculated between the MEs and weight and viremia in the serum on specific days. For weight, this was done at 0, 7, 14, 19/21, 28, 35 and 40/42 dpi, for viremia days examined were 4, 7, 11, 14 and 19/21 dpi.
